        <li><strong>Niche:</strong> Purists who prioritize nicotine hit over flavour complexity.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>ICEBERG</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Flavours:</strong> 13+ products at SnusFriend; aggressive fruit/berry range.</li>
        <li><strong>Strengths:</strong> 6-40mg range (some variants higher elsewhere).</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture:</strong> Consistent and well-balanced.</li>
        <li><strong>Niche:</strong> Experienced users who want strength plus interesting flavours.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>The Verdict</h3>
      <p>Choose <strong>Pablo</strong> if you want flavour diversity at extreme strengths. Choose <strong>Siberia</strong> if you're a hardcore minimalist seeking pure nicotine. Choose <strong>ICEBERG</strong> if you want a balanced blend of strength and flavour variety.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>Are Pablo nicotine pouches safe?</h3>
      <p>Pablo pouches are legal in most EU markets and manufactured to strict standards. However, high-strength variants—especially 50mg—carry significant risks including nicotine poisoning. They are NOT safe for beginners, pregnant women, or those without nicotine tolerance. Always consult healthcare providers and start with lower strengths.</p>

      <h3>What is the strongest Pablo nicotine pouch?</h3>
      <p>Pablo's 50mg variants are among the strongest pouches on the market. These are designed only for experienced users with established nicotine tolerance. Starting at 50mg can cause severe nicotine poisoning.</p>

      <h3>Are Pablo pouches available in the UK?</h3>
      <p>Availability varies by region and changes frequently due to regulatory updates. Check SnusFriend for current stock and shipping eligibility to your location.</p>

      <h3>How long do Pablo pouches last?</h3>
      <p>Most Pablo pouches last 30-60 minutes depending on your personal absorption rate and the strength. Higher-strength varieties may feel shorter due to intensity.</p>

      <h3>What's the best Pablo flavour for beginners?</h3>
      <p>Pablo is NOT recommended for beginners at all. If you must try Pablo, start with their Silver strength (10mg) in a familiar flavour like Frosted Mint. However, we recommend beginners choose brands specifically designed for entry-level users.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Final Thoughts</h2>
      <p>Pablo represents the extreme end of the nicotine pouch spectrum. It's a brand for users who have graduated far beyond casual nicotine consumption and actively seek the most powerful options available. The 30+ flavours prove that extreme strength doesn't mean sacrificing taste, and the cult following among experienced users speaks to genuine quality and consistency.</p>
      <p>But this is not a casual endorsement. Pablo demands respect, self-awareness about your own nicotine tolerance, and honest assessment of risk. A 50mg pouch is not a typical consumer product—it's a tool for experienced users managing specific nicotine needs.</p>
      <p>If you're exploring Pablo, start low (10mg), stay hydrated, and never use more than one pouch per day as you learn your tolerance. And if you're entirely new to nicotine pouches, please choose a gentler brand first.</p>
